			"type": "text",
			"text": "Tariccoia comes from the Ordovician, with fossils found in the Monte Argentu Formation, Sardinia, Italy, and the Fezouata Formation, Morocco. It is a small, elongated liwiid and grew up to 6 cm in length. Unlike other liwiids, which have short rounded pygidiums, Tariccoia has a more elongated pointed one, which also bears a more pronounced mid-ridge. The generic name derives from the Latinised surname of M. Taricco, a palaeontologist from Sardinia, Italy."
